For now, the header component should include the product name and a "Save" button.  Prior art can be seen in [this PR](https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/pull/36921).

The save button should be disabled when saving or when the post saving has been locked:

```
const { isPostSavingLocked, isSaving } = useSelect(
	( select ) => {
		return {
			isPostSavingLocked:
				select( 'core/editor' ).isPostSavingLocked(),
			isSaving: select( 'core' ).isSavingEntityRecord(
				'postType',
				'product',
				product?.id
			),
		};
	},
	[ product?.id ]
);

const isDisabled = isPostSavingLocked || isSaving;

<Button
	onClick={ handleSave }
	variant="primary"
	isBusy={ isSaving }
	disabled={ isDisabled }
>
	{ __( 'Save', 'woocommerce' ) }
</Button>
```

